<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-2801] SecurityHandler does not tolerate plain-text COSString</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2801</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SecurityHandler does not handle the possibility, that a COSString is already plain text if the document is encrypted. This patch makes it tolerant when decrypting COSString, so that if it fails it just logs that and keeps the original content. The code works with all files I have.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12829682">PDFBOX-2801</key>
            <summary>SecurityHandler does not tolerate plain-text COSString</summary>
