                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14544213" author="tilman" created="Thu, 14 May 2015 19:10:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; any opinion about the 2nd part of the patch? I already committed the 1st part in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2576&quot; title=&quot;Improve code quality&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2576&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2576&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, that patch part is based on a remark I made in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2796&quot; title=&quot;SecurityHandler should not try to decrypt TU entries&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2796&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2796&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I would commit the 2nd part too, although I&apos;d change the debug log into a warning log but I&apos;d like your opinion first.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14548340" author="lehmi" created="Mon, 18 May 2015 17:24:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m won&apos;t apply that patch without having a look at an affected pdf. Maybe a crypt filter is used which can be configured to or not to encrypt streams and/or strings.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14548465" author="briksoftware" created="Mon, 18 May 2015 18:25:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I produced a document with a similar issue. Acrobat opens it without complaint, but PDFBox without the patch failed on it because the length of the string is not a multiple of the block size. This only happens with AES of course, with RC4 there is no block size so no exception is thrown. If you want to analyze the file, only the &quot;Author&quot; attribute at the end of the file is corrupted (I deleted one byte).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch fixes the behavior and makes it like Acrobat and Preview from OS X (since Preview does not support the XML-based version of the metadata, it shows garbage in the Author field, as it should be, Acrobat apparently reads the XML instead).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14550159" author="lehmi" created="Tue, 19 May 2015 10:01:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, but that&apos;s not the same. The origin report adresses not encrypted fields in an encrypted pdf. Your sample on the contrary is a manually corrupted pdf.&lt;br/&gt;
Maybe my former comment wasn&apos;t that clear. We should check if your file is malformed or not. Is the mentioned &quot;TU&quot; entry the one and only field which isn&apos;t encrypted? Does the encryption dictionary contain any &quot;StmF&quot; or &quot;StrF&quot; entries? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14556466" author="briksoftware" created="Fri, 22 May 2015 17:19:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;wrong object&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14556472" author="briksoftware" created="Fri, 22 May 2015 17:23:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are right it is not the same thing, but is another use-case for the patch (tolerance of corrupted files). I attached a screenshot of the plaintext object from the file, since I cannot post the entire file. I see no StmF or StrF there, but I might be missing something.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14556482" author="lehmi" created="Fri, 22 May 2015 17:35:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You hit the nail on the head. The TU is part of the signature dictionary which isn&apos;t encrypted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please replace in SecurityHandler#decryptDictionary the following line&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!COSName.SIG.equals(dictionary.getItem(COSName.TYPE)))&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;with&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!COSName.SIG.equals(dictionary.getItem(COSName.FT)))&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14556493" author="briksoftware" created="Fri, 22 May 2015 17:41:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed, this makes it work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14556523" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 22 May 2015 18:01:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1681174 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1681174&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1681174&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2801&quot; title=&quot;SecurityHandler does not tolerate plain-text COSString&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2801&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2801&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: use the correct name to detect signature dictionaries&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14556533" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 22 May 2015 18:09:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1681178 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1681178&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1681178&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2801&quot; title=&quot;SecurityHandler does not tolerate plain-text COSString&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2801&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2801&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: there are 2 possible kinds of signature dictionaries&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14556535" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 22 May 2015 18:12:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1681179 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/1.8&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1681179&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1681179&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2801&quot; title=&quot;SecurityHandler does not tolerate plain-text COSString&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2801&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2801&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: there are 2 possible kinds of signature dictionaries&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14556541" author="lehmi" created="Fri, 22 May 2015 18:14:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are obviously 2 different kinds of signature dictionaries. The SIG value is stored in different fields (TYPE vs. FT)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report and the input!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15067971" author="tilman" created="Tue, 22 Dec 2015 11:20:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=briksoftware&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;briksoftware&quot;&gt;briksoftware&lt;/a&gt; I&apos;ve added you as a watcher on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3173&quot; title=&quot;Signature dictionary is not decrypted in encrypted files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3173&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-3173&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. When that one is done, please retest your files.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
